    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "the issue with having too many peers (>55) is lodestar doesn't control which peers to remove, it's decided randomly by libp2p https://github.com/libp2p/js-libp2p/blob/v0.39.2/src/connection-manager/index.ts#L635 since we don't have any tagging strategy. It does not happen with `unstable/stable` branch because peers are consistently at 50. When peers are >50 but <= 55, it's decided by lodestar's pruning strategy.\r\n\r\nalso lodestar could consider more outbound peers, right now the ratio is 0.1 in lodestar (`OUTBOUND_PEERS_RATIO`) while lighthouse (`TARGET_OUTBOUND_ONLY_FACTOR`) is 0.3\r\n\r\n",
